:"https://www.homedepot.com/c/ah/how-to-troubleshoot-a-garage-door/9ba683603be9fa5395fab90f1213f39";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.homedepot.com";}i:18;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:32:"garage door light keeps blinking";s:4:"slug";s:32:"garage-door-light-keeps-blinking";s:5:"title";s:64:"Reasons Why You Re Garage Door Light Isn T Working How To Fix It";s:3:"alt";s:23:"garage door specialists";s:3:"url";s:72:"https://www.garagedoorspecialists.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/ATS.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTEK5VYj6v3EHT4dfo-aXTG0Xp3BVEf22UOADo-CGRAyVd1FMuo5pMfp67SJI5Aq4rymDw";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:502;s:6:"height";i:751;s:6:"source";s:72:"https://www.garagedoorspecialists.com/blog/fix-broken-garage-door-light/";s:6:"domain";s:29:"www.garagedoorspecialists.com";}i:19;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:32:"garage door light keeps blinking";s:4:"slug";s:32:"garage-door-light-keeps-blinking";s:5:"title";s:74:"Troubleshooting A Garage Door That Won T Close Champion Garage Door Repair";s:3:"alt";s:27:"champion garage door repair";s:3:"url";s:89:"https://garagedoorchamp.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/Garage-Door-Sensors-Terminal-1.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcT1AEx9U6hiwR5TjXSSbM0NFrkSPg-Qk-cGvXImobPlIqfvHuNSlnXusB6wBZSK3UzLQgw";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:335;s:6:"height";i:553;s:6:"source";s:67:"https://garagedoorchamp.com/troubleshooting-garage-door-wont-close/";s:6:"domain";s:19:"garagedoorchamp.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:32:"garage door light keeps blinking";s:4:"slug";s:32:"garage-door-light-keeps-blinking";s:5:"title";s:60:"Linear Garage Door Opener Troubleshooting Step By Step Guide";s:3:"alt";s:60:"linear garage door opener troubleshooting step by step guide";s:3:"url";s:97:"http://garageadviser.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Linear-Garage-Door-Opener-Troubleshooting.png";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQQT6jEvw0Gg8Afmq6zTF4ZWSa8E6ANsFWvlw";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"png";s:5:"width";i:315;s:6:"height";i:560;s:6:"source";s:68:"https://garageadviser.net/linear-garage-door-opener-troubleshooting/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"garageadviser.net";}}s:9:"sentences";a:60:{i:0;s:194:"The first thing youll want to do when your garage door light is blinking is to check to see if the lock button sometimes referred to as the Vacation button is turned on and if it is turn it off.";i:1;s:61:"Start by locating the lock button on your garage door opener.";i:2;s:27:"If youre unsure where this.";i:3;s:28:"Light Blinking Continuously.";i:4;s:165:"If you own a new garage door opener that comes with a locking feature its possible someone may have accidentally locked your garage door by pressing the lock button.";i:5;s:150:"If you try to open your door using a remote while the lock system is engaged youll notice that the garage door light will begin blinking continuously.";i:6;s:27:"Replacement Safety Sensors.";i:7;s:124:"Httpsamznto2YUuWGvWith this short video I will show you how to get your garage door closed when the light is flashing 10 ti.";i:8;s:44:"Why is my garage door sensor blinking green.";i:9;s:96:"Green lights mean the sensors are working while red lights indicate the sensors are not aligned.";i:10;s:94:"If you see red lights try inspecting the bracket or tightening a screw on the blinking sensor.";i:11;s:103:"Youll know you fixed the sensor if the light stops blinking and your garage door closes properly again.";i:12;s:122:"Four flashes is the most common reason your opener lights may be flashing is because of your sensor eyes being misaligned.";i:13;s:125:"If an object has misaligned your sensor eyes then it breaks the electronic beam preventing the garage door to close properly.";i:14;s:44:"The door will stop and reverse back upwards.";i:15;s:91:"I entered the garage and the light bulbs in the unit were flashing on and off continuously.";i:16;s:111:"I unplugged the unit and plugged it back in to see if it would reset the opener but the same problem persisted.";i:17;s:140:"I know that the lights blinking a certain number of times indicate a specific problem but mine are blinking continuously and extremely fast.";i:18;s:179:"Garage Door Wall Switch Light Blinking The garage door opener flashing wall button is completely different from photo cell led light being outor the motor head led light flashing.";i:19;s:55:"For some units lockout mode produces a flashing button.";i:20;s:80:"The locking mechanism protects access to the garage by disabling the power unit.";i:21;s:54:"Simply so why is my garage door opener light flashing.";i:22;s:99:"The blinking opener lights indicate that the safety sensors are likely blocked or out of alignment.";i:23;s:96:"Defective safety sensors or faulty sensor wiring also cause the opener lights to blink 10 times.";i:24;s:107:"The safety sensors use an invisible beam of infrared light to detect obstructions in the garage doors path.";i:25;s:83:"My Craftsman garage door opener wall control is blinking and the remotes dont work.";i:26;s:141:"The garage door opener flashing wall button is completely different from photo-cell LED light being out or the motor head LED light flashing.";i:27;s:197:"The constantly flashing wall button simply means that the door was either put into lock-out mode by someone using the wall panel control or for some reason it defaulted into lock-out mode in error.";i:28;s:82:"The light from the opener blinks 10 times to warn you about misaligned photo eyes.";i:29;s:211:"To fix this issue first locate the two photo eyes attached to your garage door and clean the lens using a soft microfiber clothLoosen the wing nut holding up the photo eye and adjust them until both sensors are.";i:30;s:148:"When you see your garage door opener lights flashing and the garage door will not close it could be the safety reversing sensors or the LOCK button.";i:31;s:75:"If there is a safety reversing sensor issue the main lights flash 10 times.";i:32;s:39:"Start with aligning the safety sensors.";i:33;s:111:"You can close the garage door by pressing and holding the door control push bar until down travel is completed.";i:34;s:55:"When the lock button is ON the garage door opener will.";i:35;s:62:"While the light is blinking press your remote button again to.";i:36;s:82:"If either spring is broken the garage door opener may struggle to lift the weight.";i:37;s:123:"Nor under the beautiful light of a morning sunrise all that is waiting for competitors in those moments is crushing defeat.";i:38;s:105:"The first thing you need to do is figure out why your garage door is constantly blinking and not closing.";i:39;s:68:"Once you find the reason you can look for a solution that will work.";i:40;s:117:"Often times this problem is easy to fix so all you need to do is replace the light bulbs that are in the door itself.";i:41;s:51:"You can usually find these at any home improvement.";i:42;s:189:"Ive had this same issue when its not the vacation lock as mentioned by someone else you can make the garage door opener blink like this if you hold down one of the remotes buttons too long.";i:43;s:72:"Then all the remotes stop working and the wall pad light blinks rapidly.";i:44;s:127:"Faulty sensors occur due to damaged wires or dirty lenses and you may wonder the cause of your garage door sensor blinking red.";i:45;s:54:"The exterior LED light blinks when the door is closed.";i:46;s:158:"The green light shows that the sensors are working while the red blinking light indicates the sensors are not aligned and there is a fault in the garage door.";i:47;s:52:"Liftmaster Garage Door Opener Yellow Light Blinking.";i:48;s:37:"Posted on June 14 2020 by Bandi Ruma.";i:49;s:182:"Garage opener light blinking a craftsman garage door opener motor not craftsman garage door opener motor not garage door opener stopped working garage door opener flashing led light.";i:50;s:38:"The Light Keeps Blinking Continuously.";i:51;s:55:"There are many reasons for the lights to keep blinking.";i:52;s:77:"If the light flashing persists then the problem may be related to the wiring.";i:53;s:117:"The same problem persists if the door opener cannot detect that the safety sensors are properly working or connected.";i:54;s:140:"If your garage door opener wont close and the motor unit lights blink 10 times it usually means you have a problem with your safety sensors.";i:55;s:143:"In this video from Sears PartsDirect well show you some simple fixes like checking the garage door openers alignment and clearing obstructions.";i:56;s:88:"Reconnect one impulse transmitter after the other and check it every time by a test run.";i:57;s:35:"The door should then start to move.";i:58;s:98:"In case the motor operates in one case by itself check the cabling searching for a faulty contact.";i:59;s:88:"If you cannot clearly determin the reason disconnect the respective impulse transmitter.";}}